{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[אהרן|אַהֲרֹן]] ''(Ahărōn)'', possibly meaning "bearer of martyrs", or perhaps also, or instead, related to the Ancient Egyptian "aha rw" ("warrior lion", though it has been suggested to also mean "elevated", "exalted" or "high mountain").

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# {{Christianity}} The elder brother of [[Moses]] in the Book of the [[Exodus]].
#{{given name|male|from Hebrew|}} A [[Biblical]] male [[given name]].

